  "texts": [
    "Each node in the graph is attributed with text: the root node is attributed with the original news content x 0, child nodes (users) are attributed with historical user posts x 𝑗, 𝑗 > 0.",
    "To constrain the text length, we limit each user to their 200 most recent posts.",
    "Ground-truth outlier labels, indicating whether the news/graph is fake (1) or real (0), are adopted from prior work.",
    "Additionally, we include the Unix timestamp for each node to capture temporal information.",
    "Preliminary experiments indicate naively put the Unix timestamp into the LLM prompt does not significantly affect detection performance."
  ],
